5:
Hear, hear!
I hereby declare the Hero Strategy
Assembly has officially begun!
14:
Well, you see, I have recently been
made aware of a certain fact.
17:
Namely that there is no singular
path to becoming a hero. There are
in fact, multiple roads one can walk!
21:
Therefore, I need your wisdom, my
friends, to answer a question:
What kind of hero shall I become?!
26:
So, you want help coming up with
ideas for your hero roleplay shtick?
31:
Yes! If there's anything consuming
Yamato media has taught me, it's
that one must work together with
one's NAKAMA to succeed!
35:
Hmm... Figuring out what kind of her
you want to be isn't easy.
39: How about like... a doctor hero?
49:
Good, good! Keep your wonderful
ideas flowing, my friends!
54:
Ooh, what about a gourmet chef
hero?
57:
Imagine, you take out a monster
and you cook 'em up—right there on
the spot! Then, you treat the person
you rescued to a delicious meal!
66:
So basically it comes down to PR
and marketing, huh. On my world,
we'd use social media to get that
done.
71:
Yeah, that sounds like Qualia City, all
right. Lots of... unique heroes over
there.
80:
I... I wish to have a cute, female
virtual avatar! A delicate, beautiful
exterior, but with ME on the inside!
85:
You wouldn't be the first guy to ever
do that. Not sure that's gonna get
anybody's attention.
89:
But perhaps if we excel in the
execution... Say, for example, an
avatar with the appearance of Lady
Primula, but with MY ninja skills!
93:
Yes, it may work! I feel the hints of a
viral sensation!
107:
How superficial and conceited of
me, to only care for my outward
appearance... I am indeed an
impostor.
112:
O-oh... So, you don't want to go
through with that idea?
116: Lady Primula, what do you mean?
120:
I... Um, I actually kind of want to give
it a try! Your avatar suggestion, I
mean.
129:
I want to challenge myself to do
new things... We are on vacation,
after all!
133:
Well, it's settled then! Time to make
this happen!
140:
No, no! I sense remnants of shame
in your composure—you must shed
them and strike a daring pose!
144: Like this! Bring your hips in like this!
154:
Very nice! You look great, Primula.
Now, look this way.
158:
Ooh, Echo, over here! Take one of us
too!
162:
Quickly, please! I don't know how
long I can hold this pose...
172: Well, this place sure is lively.
176:
Are they taking photographs of
each other?
181:
Yeah, though it started out as a
shoot to grab assets for Primula's VR
model.
186:
Then all of a sudden it turned into
everyone doing hero poses.
195:
Oh! Lady Stella. Would you and your
cohort like to join the shoot?
200:
My legs are killing me, but it's still
super fun! With Shota's help, we can
even do poses mid-air! It's so cool!
210:
I feel like everyone forgot why we
started doing this in the first place.
214:
Eh, it's no big deal. Let them have
fun, I say.
218:
Indeed. Summer is the perfect time
for laughter and cheer like this. I'm
positive this will lift their spirits.
223:
Doesn't it just bring a tear to your
eye, watching your kids all grown up,
pops?
227:
Wh-what?! I am NOT their father—or
anyone's!
232:
Lady Bulleta! I wish to immortalize
your image in the form of a cool
pose as well!
236:
Uh, sorry, that's not really my cup of
tea.
241:
I anticipated you would feel that
way—it's very much in line with your
COOL personality, after all!
246:
But I must entreat you once again,
this time with greater passion.
253:
PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE POSE FOR ME!
I'M BEGGING YOU, PLEASE, JUST DO
THIS FOR ME, PLEASE!
258:
Man, you really love flinging yourself
at the ground like that, huh...
263:
Ayumu! The hell are you standing
over there for? Get over here and
join us!
267:
Light, Nimbus, don't think you guys
are getting out of this either! Come
on over!
273:
Hold on... With all these members...
we could form our own superhero
squadron!
277:
Uh, pretty sure we've got way too
many people for that.
281:
Some people can be reserves!
Come now, everyone! Strike your
finest pose alongside me!
